Title: The Finiteness Requirement for Six-Dimensional Euclidean Einstein

GravityAuthors: G.W.Gibbons and S.Ichinose

Comments: 15 pages, Introduction is improved, many figures(eps)

Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 17 (2000) 2129-2138

The finiteness requirement for Euclidean Einstein gravity is shown to be sostringent that only the flat metric is allowed. We examine counterterms in 4Dand 6D Ricci-flat manifolds from general invariance arguments.